article.headline: Maine 57, Kennesaw State 51
article.story: ORONO, Maine -- Gerald McElmore made six 3-pointers and scored 20 points to lead Maine to a 57-51 victory over Kennesaw State on Sunday. McElmore, who entered with 30 3-pointers in eight games, was 6-for-10 from beyond the arc to help the Black Bears (5-4) win for the third time in four games. Maine led throughout the second half, but Kennesaw State (4-5) cut the lead to 37-31 on Kurtis Woods' free throw with 11:55 left. McElmore countered with a 3-pointer and Troy Barnies hit a free throw to push the margin to 41-31 with 11:46 remaining. Barnies, who had 11 points and 13 rebounds, hit a 3-pointer to give Maine a 47-34 lead with 6:24 to play. Kennesaw State, which was 19-for-25 on 3-pointers in a 97-91 win over Lipscomb on Dec. 5, was 5-for-29 (17.2 percent) against Maine. Markeith Cummings and Matt Heramb led the Owls with 11 points each. LaDaris Green had 15 rebounds.
